{
  "stem": "1975.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then the Gestapo came with-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Rauca was at that time the head of the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he came with a group of Nazis, with dogs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they used to-- the selection-- go to the left, or go to the right.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we found out right away-- you didn't have to be a genius to find out that those who were going to the left are going to be taken out from the ghetto somewhere.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody knew where or what.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But-- because based on the composition-- they were all elderly people, children, too young people to work.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, they-- those who were able to work, they put them to the right.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they took me to the right.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I had my grandmother, who was that time in the-- close to 60.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when the German turned away, I pulled her back over to my side.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And fortunately, you know, there was such a mass of people, that they-- they hardly-- But then they separated, took out, about 10,000 people, 12,000 people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they took them out, and they took them also to the Ninth Fort.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they-- they-- they were killed in the-- the next-- the next day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the ghetto became an--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was the first selection.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was the first-- the first large selection.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then they had-- then they-- we had a small ghetto where we had a hospital, where we had to cross a bridge over this street, [BACKROUND NOISE] because they made the certain streets, certain roads-- they-- there was very-- they had movement, and they were just not able to include them in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 54
    }
  ],
